          "text": "- **P0 — Root-element capture misses real story UI rendered through portals.** The spec requires capturing “the Storybook root” ([design:82](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:82)), but this repo renders dialogs, tooltips, selects, popovers, sheets, and menus into `document.body` portals—for example [dialog.tsx:79](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/packages/ui/src/components/dialog.tsx:79) and [tooltip.tsx:89](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/packages/ui/src/components/tooltip.tsx:89). A `#storybook-root` locator screenshot would silently omit the most important state of those stories. Specify viewport-level `page.screenshot()` after asserting the root exists, and add an integration fixture proving an opened portal appears in the candidate.\n\n- **P1 — Baseline compatibility data is recorded per run but not persisted with the approved baseline.** Only `baseline.png` is committed while `result.json` is ignored ([design:127](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:127)); `environmentKey` omits browser revision, host platform, comparator policy, and schema version ([design:85](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:85)); revision/platform are merely printed in run output ([design:229](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:229)). That makes the stated “same Playwright version and font set” requirement unenforceable and contradicts the research recommendation to commit stable baseline metadata ([research:63](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/research/2026-07-20-storybook-local-visual-testing-prior-art/README.md:63), [research:86](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/research/2026-07-20-storybook-local-visual-testing-prior-art/README.md:86)). Persist minimal metadata beside each baseline and define/test whether incompatible approval or comparison warns or fails.\n\n- **P1 — Render/readiness signaling is underspecified enough to permit a race.** The runner must await Storybook render and `play` completion ([design:93](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:93)), but the package anatomy defines no preview annotation or pre-navigation instrumentation that can observe those events ([design:32](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:32)). Subscribing after iframe navigation can miss an immediate render/play event and timeout valid stories. Specify the pre-navigation observation mechanism and add integration cases for immediate render, delayed `play`, render error, and play error.\n\n- **P1 — Storybook status semantics have no defined mapping.** The engine has `passed`, `new`, `changed`, `capture-error`, and `removed` ([design:146](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:146)), while the manager promises test-provider/sidebar projection ([design:198](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:198)). The spec never defines how those states map to Storybook’s smaller status vocabulary, and `removed` has no current story entry to annotate. Define the projection explicitly and test each mapping; keep `removed` panel-only.\n\n- **P2 — Static Storybook behavior is ambiguous.** Mutations and artifact serving depend on the Node/server channel ([design:214](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:214)), yet verification requires a Storybook build and merely says the addon “loads” ([design:268](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-20-local-storybook-visual-tests-design.md:268), [design:289](/home/leon0399/Projects/llame/docs/superpowers/specs/2026-07-